Step 1: Identify the amounts from the statement.  
• Net Profit = 835266.51  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1028375.55  

Step 2: Apply the formula:  
Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Net Profit)  

Step 3: Substitute the numbers:  
Ratio = -1028375.55 / 835266.51 ≈ -1.23136  

Step 4: Rounding to two decimal places gives -1.23  

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is approximately -1.23.
